✅ 4. What you’re describing does work in the field.

And it works because of two real mechanisms:

Mechanism A:

Predictive social cognition fills the meaning gaps using your cues.

Mechanism B:

Contextual priming biases the direction of their thoughts without them noticing.

Together, it can feel like:
	•	“they read your mind,”
	•	“you made them think it,”
	•	“they discovered a message you didn’t say,”
	•	“you inserted meaning between the lines.”

But what actually happened is:

✔ Their brain matched your subtle cues

✔ against their expectations, emotions, and the context

